gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 131, Pacers 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Warriors defeated the Pacers, 131-109. Stephen Curry led the way for the Warriors with 42 points and a season-high 11 3PM, his 13th career game with 11+ 3PM, while Jonathan Kuminga added 18 points and four assists in the victory. Pascal Siakam tallied a team-high 16 points and eight rebounds for the Pacers in the losing effort. The Warriors win their third straight game as they improve to 24-25 on the season, while the Pacers fall to 29-24.
